<HI>form</HI> our selves according to such a Pattern, where
there appears no <HI>Impossibility,</HI> as there does in the
other, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">f becoming like it.</P>
<P>This <HI>Poem</HI> seems to me to abound in all kinds of
<HI>Beauties,</HI> which are admir'd in Poetical <HI>Writings.</HI> What
noble strains of Eloquence occurr in every place where
