<HI>Poems</HI> before-mention'd; yet this seems an <HI>Inven|tion</HI>
of their own. For as the <HI>Learned Man</HI> be|fore-mentioned
observes, 'tis scarce possible to relate
any wonderful <HI>Action</HI> of a Great Person, or any con|siderable
<HI>Occurrence,</HI> but 'twill be very easie to draw
<PB REF="11">
some <HI>Moral Inference</HI> from it, tho' the <HI>Writer</HI> ne|ver
