should be so far enamour'd with the Pagan <HI>Wri|tings,</HI>
as to form themselves entirely by their Patterns,
to be taken up with the <HI>Study</HI> of them to the <HI>total
neglect</HI> of these <HI>inspir'd Writings.</HI> What pains and
labour have our Men been at, how great a part of
